<?xml version="1.0"?>
<package xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <metadata>
    <id>calibre</id>
    <title>Calibre</title>
    <version>0.9.32</version>
    <authors>Kovid Goyal</authors>
    <owners>Gary Ewan Park</owners>
    <summary>calibre is the one stop solution to all your e-book needs.</summary>
    <description>calibre is a free and open source e-book library management application developed by users of e-books for users of e-books.</description>
    <projectUrl>http://calibre-ebook.com/</projectUrl>
    <tags>ebook library management</tags>
    <copyright>Kovid Goyal</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.ico</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: Show the number of currently selected books in the status bar at the bottom of the book list
    - New: Driver for PocketBook Touch 623 and Yarvik tablet Xenta 13c
	- New: When editing dates such as published, allow pressing the minus key to clear the date and the = key to set the date to today.
    - Fixed: EPUB/AZW3 Output: Fix regression that caused erros when trying to convert documents that have URLs with invalid (non-utf-8) quoting.
    - Fixed: When backing up metadata automatically remove XML invalid chars, instead of erroring out
    - Fixed: ebook-viewer: Fix --debug-javascript option causing an error when running from a binary build on os x and linux
    - Fixed: Fix switch library dialog and menu both popping up when clicking the library button in some window managers
	- Fixed: Apple driver: Fix a regression in 0.9.31 that could cause sending books to the device to hang
	- Fixed: When setting metadata using the edit metadata dialog, convert newlines, tabs etc. to normal spaces
	- Fixed: EPUB/AZW3 Output: Fix pages that contain only an svg image being regarded as empty and removed during splitting
	- Fixed: AZW3 Input: Handle files that use unnecessary svg: prefixes.
	- Fixed: EPUB Input: Handle EPUB files that have no metadata section in their OPF.
	- Fixed: Get Books: Fix Foyles UK store plugin.
	- New News Source: WirtschaftsWoche Online by Hegi
    - Improved News Source: Wall Street Journal
    - Improved News Source: Various Polish news sources
	- Improved News Source: Handelsblatt
	- Improved News Source: The Australian
	- Improved News Source: Las Vegas Review
	- Improved News Source: NME
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
